<recipe>
    <name>Standing Crusted Rib Roast</name>
    <indexCharacter>S</indexCharacter>
    <notes>Preheat oven to 325 degrees</notes>
    <servings>12</servings>
    <instructions>In a hot skillet melt your 2 tablespoons of whole butter and sear the rib roast on all sides until it is browned. Place the rib roast in your roasting pan. Salt and pepper to taste. In a mixing bowl add your horseradish, breadcrumbs, garlic, parsley, paprika and melted butter. Mix well. Using your hand coat the rib roast with the crust as evenly as possible until you have used all your crust mix. Place the cut vegetables in the roasting pan around the rib roast. Add your water. Cook roast according to Siesel's directions.</instructions>
